Prints Model Halfnormal Summary

# S3 method for auditor_model_halfnormal
print(x, ...)

Arguments

...

other parameters

Examples

titanic <- na.omit(DALEX::titanic[1:100,])

# fit a model
model_glm <- glm(survived ~ ., family = binomial, data = titanic)

# use DALEX package to wrap up a model into explainer
exp_glm <- DALEX::explain(model_glm)
#> Preparation of a new explainer is initiated
#>   -> model label       :  lm  (  default  )
#>   -> data              :  98  rows  9  cols  extracted from the model  
#>   -> target variable   :  not specified! (  WARNING  )
#>   -> model_info        :  package stats , ver. 4.0.0 , task classification (  default  ) 
#>   -> predict function  :  yhat.glm  will be used (  default  )
#>   -> predicted values  :  numerical, min =  1.721693e-09 , mean =  0.3673469 , max =  1  
#>   -> residual function :  difference between y and yhat (  default  )
#>   A new explainer has been created!  

# validate a model with auditor
library(auditor)
model_halfnormal(exp_glm)
#> Binomial model 
#> Model label:  
#> Quantiles of Residuals:

#> -2.0268310187 -0.9891191280 -0.7507466977 -0.6184924338 -0.4052881806 
#>           50%           60%           70%           80%           90% 
#> -0.1205808471 -0.0001199433  0.5731707308  0.7043099673  1.1881626328 
#>          100% 
#>  2.2775116447
